<p>Welcome to the Molecular Cytology Core Facility intranet pages. We provide consulation, training and technical assistance in a range of technologies:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="autohistology.html">Automated Histology</a>: immunohistochemistry, immunofluorescence, RNA <em>in situ</em> hybridization, and TUNEL assays</li>
  <li><a href="manualhistology.html">Manual Histology</a>: fixation, embedding, sectioning and IHC, UF and RNA <em>in situ</em> hybridization</li>
  <li><a href="microscopy.html">Microscopy</a>: widefield, confocal and atomic force microscopy, live and time-lapse imaging, and image processing/analysis.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="to-become-a-user">To become a user</h2>
<p>Go to <a href="https://ilab.mskcc.org">iLab</a>, sign in using your MSKCC ID and password, and follow the instructions. A confirmation email will be sent to your PI, which they must sign off on. For any questions, contact <a href="mailto:mccf@mskcc.org">mccf@mskcc.org</a>.</p>

<h2 id="to-use-our-facility">To use our facility</h2>
<p>For microscopy and histology experiments, sign up on <a href="https://ilab.mskcc.org">iLab</a>. A list of charges can be found on our <a href="charges">charges page</a>.</p>

<p>For staining experiments, please fill out our <a href="downloads/submissionform.pdf">submission form</a>. FILL IN REST OF POLICY HERE.</p>

<p>Our cancellation and co-authorship/acknowledgement policies can be found on our <a href="policies.html">policies page</a></p>
